description: Gets the Integrations for an API.

nested_items.name: ApiGatewayManaged
nested_items.description: Specifies whether an integration is managed by API Gateway. If you created an API using using quick create, the resulting integration is managed by API Gateway. You can update a managed integration, but you can't delete it.

nested_items.name: ConnectionId
nested_items.description: The ID of the VPC link for a private integration. Supported only for HTTP APIs.

nested_items.name: ConnectionType
nested_items.description: The type of the network connection to the integration endpoint. Specify INTERNET for connections through the public routable internet or VPC_LINK for private connections between API Gateway and resources in a VPC. The default value is INTERNET.

nested_items.name: ContentHandlingStrategy
nested_items.description: Supported only for WebSocket APIs. Specifies how to handle response payload content type conversions. Supported values are CONVERT_TO_BINARY and CONVERT_TO_TEXT, with the following behaviors:

nested_items.name: CredentialsArn
nested_items.description: Specifies the credentials required for the integration, if any. For AWS integrations, three options are available. To specify an IAM Role for API Gateway to assume, use the role's Amazon Resource Name (ARN). To require that the caller's identity be passed through from the request, specify the string arn:aws:iam:::user/. To use resource-based permissions on supported AWS services, specify null.

nested_items.name: Description
nested_items.description: Represents the description of an integration.

nested_items.name: IntegrationId
nested_items.description: Represents the identifier of an integration.

nested_items.name: IntegrationMethod
nested_items.description: Specifies the integration's HTTP method type.

nested_items.name: IntegrationResponseSelectionExpression
nested_items.description: The integration response selection expression for the integration. Supported only for WebSocket APIs. See Integration Response Selection Expressions.

nested_items.name: IntegrationSubtype
nested_items.description: Supported only for HTTP API AWS_PROXY integrations. Specifies the AWS service action to invoke. To learn more, see Integration subtype reference.

nested_items.name: IntegrationType
nested_items.description: The integration type of an integration. One of the following:

nested_items.name: IntegrationUri
nested_items.description: For a Lambda integration, specify the URI of a Lambda function.

nested_items.name: PassthroughBehavior
nested_items.description: Specifies the pass-through behavior for incoming requests based on the Content-Type header in the request, and the available mapping templates specified as the requestTemplates property on the Integration resource. There are three valid values: WHEN_NO_MATCH, WHEN_NO_TEMPLATES, and NEVER. Supported only for WebSocket APIs.

nested_items.name: PayloadFormatVersion
nested_items.description: Specifies the format of the payload sent to an integration. Required for HTTP APIs. Supported values for Lambda proxy integrations are 1.0 and 2.0. For all other integrations, 1.0 is the only supported value. To learn more, see Working with AWS Lambda proxy integrations for HTTP APIs.

nested_items.name: RequestParameters
nested_items.description: For WebSocket APIs, a key-value map specifying request parameters that are passed from the method request to the backend. The key is an integration request parameter name and the associated value is a method request parameter value or static value that must be enclosed within single quotes and pre-encoded as required by the backend. The method request parameter value must match the pattern of method.request.{location}.{name}

nested_items.name: NextToken
nested_items.description: The next page of elements from this collection. Not valid for the last element of the collection.
